com.koverse.sdk.ingest.format

Class AbstractLongLivedRecordStream<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.koverse.sdk.ingest.format.AbstractRecordStream<T>
      • com.koverse.sdk.ingest.format.AbstractLongLivedRecordStream<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of data that is streamed.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    RawRecordStream<T>, Closeable, AutoCloseable

    public abstract class AbstractLongLivedRecordStream<T>
extends AbstractRecordStream<T>
    Partial impl of a record stream that is long-lived, that is, it will always return records until it is cancelled.

    Functions by working off of a blocking queue, which is fed records from a separate thread.
